import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of x?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='x', y='y', hue='distance', palette='viridis', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('Is there a correlation between distance and x or y?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(title='Distance', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
